Date: Wed, 14 Mar 2012 17:12:42 +0100
Subject: drm/radeon: Restrict offset for legacy display engine.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 0349af70da5e590793986a0e03dbf2a435f75103
Patch-mainline: v3.4-rc1

The hardware only takes 27 bits for the offset, so larger offsets are
truncated, and the display shows random bits other than the intended ones.

Signed-off-by: Michel DÃ¤nzer <michel.daenzer@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Michal Srb <msrb@suse.com>
